  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "A great job has been done in [release-v2.1.0-solc-0.5](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/tree/release-v2.1.0-solc-0.5) to bring all contracts to 0.5. However, I stumbled upon one `address` variable that should probably be `address payable`. There might be more.\r\n\r\n[Owner](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/release-v2.1.0-solc-0.5/contracts/ownership/Ownable.sol#L9) of an `Owanble` contract is expected to receive funds in nemerous cases such as self destruction (e.g `selfdestruct(owner());`), or whenever contract's owner need to withdraw its balance. Hence, owner's address needs to be declared `payable`.\r\n\r\nI'm working on a PR against `release-v2.1.0-solc-0.5` branch now.",
